# {{.ProviderShortName}} Provider

Declaratively manage FreeSWITCH — SIP users, dialplans/IVRs, gateways,
mod_callcenter queues and mod_conference rooms — as Terraform resources.

## ⚠️ Requires the FreeSWITCH IaC control-plane

**This provider does nothing on its own.** It is a thin Terraform client for
the **FreeSWITCH IaC control-plane** — a Go API service that stores desired
state in PostgreSQL and serves it to FreeSWITCH via `mod_xml_curl`. Every
resource here is a call to that API; without a reachable control-plane,
`terraform plan`/`apply` will fail to connect.

```
Terraform  ─►  terraform-provider-freeswitch  ─►  Control-Plane API (Go)
                                                       │         ▲
                                         XML renderers │         │ ESL
                                                       ▼         │
                                          PostgreSQL    FreeSWITCH (mod_xml_curl)
```

Before using this provider you must deploy and run the control-plane (Docker
Compose: PostgreSQL + the API) and point FreeSWITCH at it. Full setup, the
server-side configuration, and end-to-end examples live in the platform repo:

**👉 https://github.com/jamalshahverdiev/freeswitch-iac-platform**

The provider talks to the control-plane's `/api/v1` over HTTPS with a bearer
token — it never connects to FreeSWITCH (ESL/SIP) directly.

